<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Attire2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Àttire,</orth> subst., dress: <cit><quote>in poor and mean a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.113" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 113</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he hath some meaning in his mad a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 126</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 257</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.133" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.8.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 8, 14</bibl>. Plural: <cit><quote>I'll show thee some --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 102</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>those --s are best,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 4.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 3, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fetch my best --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.228" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 228</bibl></cit>.
